==English==
===Verb===
# Past and past participle of to [[conjoin]].
===Adjective===
'''conjoined'''

# Joined together, as with [[conjoined twins]], or in matrimony.
#:'''1600''' ''If either of you know any inward impediment, why you should not be '''conjoined''', I charge you, on your souls, to utter it.'' — Shakespeare, ''Much Ado About Nothing'', [[s:Much_Ado_About_Nothing#Scene_1._The_Inside_of_a_Church.|Act 4, Scene 1]].

====Usage note====
'''Conjoint''' is often used, but '''conjoined''' is the preferred usage.